	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-10-02T10:07:35">North Midland Construction PLC is a civil engineering and building contractor. The Company provides design, build, operation and maintenance services across sectors covering civil engineering, building, mechanical and electrical engineering and specialist product manufacturing sectors. It operates through two business segments: PLC and Nomenca. The PLC segment includes Building and Civil Engineering, Highways, Utilities and NMCNomenca divisions. The Nomenca segment offers mechanical and electrical engineering products and services. The Company delivers design and builds projects for the public and private sector, including social housing associations, private developers, education, retail, leisure and commercial, power, waste to energy and food processing. It provides highway, bridge structures and public realm schemes across public and private sectors. The Company also offers utility diversion and installation works for the telecommunications, high speed fiber and energy providers.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2016-01-12T22:37:20">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 June 2015, North Midland Construction plc revenues increased 18% to L107.2M. Net income decreased 59% to L136K. Revenues reflect Highways segment increase from L7.7M to L18.8M, Nomenca segment increase of 26% to L23.9M, Utilites segment increase of 20% to L13.2M. Net income was offset by Utilites segment loss totaling L829K vs. income of L140K, NMC Nomenca segment income decrease of 24% to L718K.</Text>
	</TextInfo>
